Bug.WithStack:
This is a rare case, but it happened to me while cleaning up some SWT code with 
the refactoring tools and I had used a few anonymous inner classes in the SWT 
code.

Before the refactoring:
Select b and Refactor->Inline Local Variable
__________________________________________________________________
import org.eclipse.jface.action.Action;

public class X {
  
  public void foo(int a){  	
  	final int b= a;
  	bar(new Action(){
		public void run() {
			System.out.println(b);
			super.run();
		}  		
  	});
  }

  public void bar(Action action){
  }

}
__________________________________________________________________

After the refactoring:
This will generate a compile error because a is used in the anonymous inner
class but is not final.
__________________________________________________________________
import org.eclipse.jface.action.Action;

public class X {
 
  public void foo(int a){
  	bar(new Action(){
		public void run() {
			System.out.println(a);
			super.run();
		}  		
  	});
  }

  public void bar(Action action){
  }

}
__________________________________________________________________
not critical for 2.0
We should fix this if it is "easy". Otherwise we leave it as it is since it is 
a rare case.
reopen
closing.
might reopen if there's more cases like this
reopen


