source_code.code:
public final void removeDebugTarget(IDebugTarget target) {
        if (target != null) {
            if (!getDebugTargets0().contains(target)) {
                getDebugTargets0().remove(target);
                fireChanged();
            }
        }
    }

Bug.WithStack:
Here is the code for Launch.removeDebugTarget (from the 0521 build):

    /**
     * @see ILaunch#removeDebugTarget(IDebugTarget)
     */
    public final void removeDebugTarget(IDebugTarget target) {
        if (target != null) {
            if (!getDebugTargets0().contains(target)) {
                getDebugTargets0().remove(target);
                fireChanged();
            }
        }
    }

The "!" should be removed so that it checks if the target is in the list.

This fix is needed since when a JDIDebugTarget is created it adds itself to the
launch.  The super adapters do not want the JDIDebugTarget showing up in
the launch.
Even better code here is:
if (getDebugTargets0().remove(target)) {
  fireChanged();
}

remove() returns whether or not the element was removed. This saves us an 
iteration over the list.

Fixed. Please verify.
Verified.

